# Confidence Calculation

## Code Line

```python id="ax50"
confidence_a_b = support_ab / support_a
```

### Explanation

Calculates confidence:
Confidence(A \rightarrow B)=\frac{Support(A\cap B)}{Support(A)}

---

## Code Line

```python id="ax51"
confidence_b_a = support_ab / support_b
```

### Explanation

Calculates reverse confidence:

```text id="ax52"
B → A
```

---

# Check Confidence Threshold

## Code Line

```python id="ax53"
if confidence_a_b >= min_confidence:
```

### Explanation

Checks if rule confidence satisfies minimum confidence.

---

## Code Line

```python id="ax54"
print(f"{a} -> {b}  Confidence = {confidence_a_b:.2f}")
```

### Explanation

Prints association rule.

Example:

```text id="ax55"
Milk -> Bread
Confidence = 0.67
```

---

## Code Line

```python id="ax56"
if confidence_b_a >= min_confidence:
```

### Explanation

Checks reverse rule confidence.

---

## Code Line

```python id="ax57"
